LOWCARB + KETO BREAKFAST ROLLUP. by @shredhappens 
.
Tag someone you would want to be eating this with… because the flavors in this do not disappoint!! Pesto, creamy eggs, avocado, and some heat from the chili flakes make this a mouth party.
.
So easy to do:
.
1.Grab some lowcarb lavash or lowcarb bread of choice as your base.
.
2.Crack two eggs in a bowl, whisk using a whisker or fork, add sea salt and pepper, then cook in some butter or olive oil on low heat. LOW AND SLOW is key, folks! It’s the secret to deliciously velvety eggs. Once it looks almost done, remove from the heat.
.
3.Slice up some tomato, avocado, and whatever fresh toppings you like.
.
4.Warm up your lowcarb lavash for a few seconds, then top with homemade pesto, add eggs, tomato, avocado, pull apart some fresh mozarella, add arugula, and top with chili flakes.
.
5.Roll it up tight.
.
6.Spray with some olive oil and heat it up on both sides till golden and crispy.
.
7.Slice in half and devour!
.
What are some of your favorite filings? I need all the ideas I can get. Make sure you save and share with a friend. .
Make it a good day 👊🏻👊🏻

Chicken in Chipotle Cream by @keto_wonder_woman
Ingredients:
2 lbs chicken (I used boneless chicken thighs this time, but this can be made with any cut).
1 lb/16 oz mushrooms
3 roma tomatoes
2 cloves garlic
2 oz onion
8 oz cream cheese (I used @lovemyphilly 1/3 less fat cream cheese)
1/2 cup sour cream
5 Chipotle peppers in adobo sauce
1/4 c avocado oil
Salt and pepper to taste
Garlic powder

Boil the tomatoes, onion and garlic until soft and blend with the cream cheese, sour cream, and Chipotle peppers and adobo sauce. Set sauce aside.
Heat up the avocado oil in a large pan, add your chicken and season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Fry the chicken until it starts to brown then add the mushrooms. Add the sauce and allow to cook for 15 minutes. Taste for salt.
I have made this recipe in different ways, so you can always play around with it.
I have made it using chicken legs and boiling the chicken first then frying, I have also made it without the tomatoes, but love it this way a lot more 😍. You can add chicken bouillon if you would like, it does add more flavor, so that's always another option ☺️.
When I make this my family enjoys it with white rice, and I usually have it with a salad. Hope you try this! 🥰

Dinner tonight is Garlic Ranch Chicken & Alfredo Broccoli 🥳 by @lowcarbfoodcourt
_________________________
We grilled some garlic ranch marinated chicken breasts for dinner with microwaved broccoli and a double batch of Alfredo Sauce (recipe below).
_________________________
Alfredo Sauce:
1 tbsp Butter
1 tsp Minced Garlic
1/2 cup Heavy Whipping Cream
2oz Cream Cheese
1/4 cup Grated Parmesan
Salt & Pepper to taste

Add ingredients one at a time in a pan over medium heat, stirring constantly until everything is melted together, about 5 or 6 minutes.

I added 1 Tbsp sour cream to the Alfredo sauce, then added the microwaved broccoli, cooked chicken, mix, serve.
